  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 2e3b85ba0ef1eac4682a23cb38907d1b, type: 3}
  m_Name: Necromancer_2
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Dialogues
  npcName: Necromancer(HURT)
  npcSprite: {fileID: 2386087392262683051, guid: 22b5220aaa001f74aa6ed0d66f7a9028, type: 3}
  dialogueLines:
  - Finally... the weight of centuries... lifted.
  - You were a quiet tool, weren't you? No questions. No hesitation. Just a loyal
    hound doing the dirty work I was too 'frail' to manage.
  - (He slams the pieces together. A purple shockwave knocks the Player back. The
    Old Man is gone; a towering Wizard in dark robes stands in his place.)
  - Listen. There are relics in that dark hole. Ancient anchors that hold this forest
    in a loop. If you have the steel to clear that place, bring the items to me.
  - The King thought breaking my staff would keep me here forever. He didn't count
    on a fool like you wandering into my trap.
  - "To leave this forest, a soul must be left behind to hold the seal. I\u2019ve
    served my time... now, it\u2019s your turn.\""
  - (The Wizard raises his glowing staff.)
  - Don't look so surprised. Every prison needs a Warden. Welcome to your eternity!
  typingSpeed: 0.05
